RailTerm is a diversified, safety oriented, rail services contractor with operations throughout North America. We provide custom service solutions to railway operators who wish to outsource mission-critical activities.
This opportunity is for you if…
…you enjoy contributing to the architecture of processes and technological solutions to support business performance.
What’s in it for you?
The opportunity to lead the implementation of critical systems and processes to support safety critical rail maintenance services;
Flexible work arrangements (work from home, reduced work cycle, flexible hours);
An incentive compensation program;
Generous group Insurance coverage;
A group RRSP with employer contribution.
The Opportunity
Reporting to the head of finance, the Leader, Business Intelligence & Processes will collaborate with our Maintenance business unit (“BU”), finance services and other stakeholders (Quality, IT) to optimize the quality and efficiency of existing business processes and act as an expert in the implementation of systems to support asset, financial and operations management. Also, the incumbent will lead the digital transformation of the maintenance business unit. Ideally, the incumbent would be based out of Ottawa, Montreal or Toronto, with occasional travel to our different business locations.
Key Responsibilities and Functions
Support the implementation of a CMMS (Computerized Asset/Maintenance Management Software):
Provide expertise in the design & implementation of a software that will enhance RailTerm’s ability to manage preventive & corrective track maintenance;
Support change management within the group; evaluate existing systems continuity after the implementation;
Maintain & update the system's existing data & configuration (assets, work orders, parts & inventory, resources & equipment, etc.);
Act as the systems’ local administrator (super-user), developing procedures and training material, troubleshooting and suggesting improvements;
Build and maintain reports that will allow management to optimize scheduling;
Leverage all systems’ functions and data to optimize material requirements and resource planning.
Maintenance and improvement of business processes:
Maintain and leverage Maintenance BU business processes (procurement, inventory, time entries, quotations, jobs, invoicing and scheduling) and the different software & data sets that support these;
Help leveraging synergies and efficiencies between the different processes and systems in place;
Ensure optimal usage & become a champion of existing business solution tools (NAV, Office 365, MS Project, SAP Concur) while consistently looking for systems or processes improvement opportunities.
Contract administration:
Support the setup of new contract invoicing mechanisms;
Master the provisions of existing contract agreements, and monitor their application;
Support terms & conditions enforcement and negotiations with suppliers.
Financial Support:
Support the head of finance in different analysis and cost controlling activities in relation with the maintenance BU;
Help develop pricing tools and review estimations prepared by the group;
Support the pricing estimation process for track maintenance & construction opportunities;
Prepare monthly sales forecasts and variances analysis, support budget and reforecast processes.
Required Skills and Qualifications
8 to 10 years of progressive experience in related functions or projects (systems implementation, business processes review, etc.);
Experience in an asset maintenance environment (ideally in the railway industry);
Bachelor’s degree in a related field (business administration, operations management or information technology) or an equivalent combination of relevant experience and education;
Demonstrated software proficiency (CMMS, Excel, ERP, MRP, BI and databases);
Exceptional analytical and conceptual thinking skills;
Ability to organize work and complete several projects simultaneously;
Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to establish and maintain effective working relationships and influence various project stakeholders;
Sense of initiative and creativity;
Demonstrated continuous improvement mindset.
